data.text:
BNP asks India to extradite PM Sheikh Hasina for trial in Bangladesh

tnn / Aug 21, 2024, 07:57 (IST)

Bangladesh's main opposition party, BNP, requested India to extradite former PM Sheikh Hasina to face charges of murder and other cases following her departure amid a student-led uprising. The BNP claimed that the charges are serious and fall under the extraditable category, urging India to uphold legal commitments under the bilateral treaty.

Will Hema panel report stop sexual abusein Mollywood?

Aug 20, 2024, 20:53 (IST)

Toxic male aggression is responsible for coercing sexual favours out of women in Kerala film industry, writes a woman filmmaker. Change won’t happen unless the predators are punished

Safari vs Fortuner: Family feud on the road leaves trail of destruction

tnn / Aug 21, 2024, 08:14 (IST)

Bindeshwar Sharma collided his Safari with his father's Fortuner in Ambernath, causing injuries to five people, two critically. His father, Satish Sharma, had visited to resolve a family dispute. The incident occurred near 7 Level Hotel, where Bindeshwar's reckless driving led to the crash. Police are investigating the case, and Bindeshwar is currently on the run.

Why India can be the perfect peacemaker in Ukraine

Aug 20, 2024, 21:01 (IST)

This is Modi’s chance to redefine Indian national interest and show global leadership, writes a British politician who advised Tony Blair & ran New Labour’s campaign

Cisco confirms job cuts, but 'painful suspense' continues for employees

timesofindia.com / Aug 21, 2024, 01:29 (IST)

Cisco's recent announcement of laying off 7% of its workforce, amounting to over 6,300 jobs, comes after earlier this year's 5% job cut affecting 4,000 employees. These cuts are part of Cisco's strategy to shift focus towards cybersecurity, cloud systems, and AI products.

Ex-India coach feels BCCI 'can't wrap Mayank Yadav up in cotton wool'

timesofindia.com / Aug 21, 2024, 08:33 (IST)

Mayank Yadav was a standout player in IPL 2024, delivering fast-paced bowling for Lucknow Super Giants before an injury cut his season short. Despite his promising performance, doubts remain about his participation in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Test series, with experts suggesting he be eased back into first-class cricket for better development and injury management.

Eye on China, India & Japan to upgrade pact to counter security challenges

tnn / Aug 21, 2024, 08:00 (IST)

India and Japan, during their 2+2 dialogue, agreed to revise their 2008 Joint Declaration on Security Cooperation to address current security challenges. They discussed Chinese assertiveness in regional seas and explored joint security cooperation with third countries. They also addressed global issues, including the Russia-Ukraine war, and reaffirmed their stance against cross-border terrorism.
